<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-faqs"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="FAQs"></span>FAQs<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759148077281"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Q1. What are the most repeated topics in SSC CGL Quantitative Aptitude?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Ans. Arithmetic topics like Time &amp; Work, Time, Speed &amp; Distance, Percentage, Profit &amp; Loss, Simple &amp; Compound Interest, Ratio &amp; Proportion, Mixture &amp; Alligation, Averages, and Number System &amp; HCF/LCM are frequently asked. Advanced Mathematics topics like Algebra, Geometry, Mensuration, Trigonometry, and Data Interpretation also appear regularly.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759148090949"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Q2. How difficult are SSC CGL Quantitative Aptitude questions in Tier 2?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Ans. Tier 2 questions are generally high difficulty. They test not just formulas but also problem-solving speed, logical reasoning, and application of concepts in slightly complex scenarios.<br/></p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759148095470"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Q3. Are there shortcut methods to solve these questions quickly?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Ans. Yes. Shortcut formulas for simple vs. compound interest, percentages, ratio calculations, HCF/LCM, and cyclicity can save valuable time in the exam.<br/></p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759148099966"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Q4. How should I prepare for repeated questions?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Ans. Focus on mastering the high-frequency topics listed above, practice previous years’ questions, and revise formulas regularly. Daily practice of SSC CGL quant practice questions improves speed and accuracy.<br/></p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759148104632"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Q5. Do I need to only memorize formulas to score well?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Ans. No. Understanding the underlying concepts is important. Memorization alone may not help in solving questions with slight twists or higher difficulty.</p> </div> </div>



